# Custom SELinux policy module to allow rsync dac_override capability.
#
# Background:
#   The rsync systemd services run as root in the rsync_t SELinux domain.
#   When syncing files owned by bblasco, rsync needs to create directories
#   and modify file ownership on the destination, which requires bypassing
#   DAC (Discretionary Access Control) checks via the dac_override capability.
#   The rsync_full_access boolean covers NFS/remote access but does not grant
#   dac_override, so a custom policy module is required.
#
# Derived from:
#   Running the backup and capturing the AVC denial with:
#     sudo ausearch -m avc -ts recent | audit2allow -M rsync-dac-override
#
#   audit2allow produced three rules, but two were marked:
#     "#!!!! This avc is allowed in the current policy"
#   meaning they are already covered by the existing Fedora SELinux policy.
#   Only the dac_override rule below is genuinely new and required.

module rsync-dac-override 1.0;

require {
    type rsync_t;
    class capability dac_override;
}

allow rsync_t self:capability dac_override;
